{"lemma":"مِقْراضِ","slug":"مِقْراضِ","root":"ق.ر.ض","root_slug":"ق-ر-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ر-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35512"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D9%82%D9%92%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B6%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scissors, snippers, shears"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Tool noun from the root ق ر ض (q r ḍ)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35512","headword_ar":"مِقْرَاضٌ","root":"qrD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqaAriyDu","text_ar":"مَقَارِيضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) and a pair thereof is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADaAni","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, K:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraAD","text_ar":"مِقْرَاض"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single blade of a pair of shears"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scissors;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which one"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clips,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cuts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and when you speak of the two together, you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADN","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as the vulgar say, but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADaAni","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) which last is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalamaAni","text_ar":"جَلَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pair of shears"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; a word, accord. to the lexicologists having no sing.; but Sb mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADN","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus using the sing. form: (M:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADN","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADaAni","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pair of shears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jlamN","text_ar":"جلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalamaAni","text_ar":"جَلَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalamN","text_ar":"قَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalamaAni","text_ar":"قَلَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jlm","text_ar":"جلم"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miqoraADN","text_ar":"مِقْرَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalamN SagiyrN","text_ar":"جَلَمٌ صَغِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small pair of shears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pair of scissors"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (JK:) 'Adee Ibn-Zeyd uses the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforataA miqoraADK","text_ar":"شَفْرَتَا مِقْرَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two blades of a pair of shears"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scissors"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in a poem; (IB;) and other poets use the sing.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mqrAD","text_ar":"مقراض"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miforaASN","text_ar":"مِفْرَاصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"f","text_ar":"ف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifies the same. (IB.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lisaAnu fulaAni miqoraADu AlA^aEoraADi","text_ar":"لِسَانُ فُلَانِ مِقْرَاضُ الاَعْرَاضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tongue of such a one is the detractor of reputations"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","M","JK","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}